1 olive oil
soy sauce
water
1 Basmati Rice
1 Plain Tofu
1 Asian Greens
1 Courgette
1 Carrot
1 Lime
1 Teriyaki Sauce
1 Ginger Paste

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with the boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes. Drain.

• Roughly chop Asian greens. Thinly slice courgette and carrot into half-moons.
• Slice lime into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine, teriyaki sauce, ginger paste, a generous squeeze of lime juice, the soy sauce and the water.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• Cut plain tofu (see ingredients) into 2cm chunks.
• Roughly chop Asian greens. Thinly slice courgette and carrot into half-moons.
• Slice lime into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine, teriyaki sauce, ginger paste, a generous squeeze of lime juice, the soy sauce and the water.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook carrot and courgette until tender, 4-5 minutes. Add Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil. Cook prawns, tossing, until pink and starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes.
• Return vegetables to the pan. Reduce heat to low, then add teriyaki sauce mixture and cook, tossing, until combined, 1 minute.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook carrot and courgette until tender, 4-5 minutes. Add Asian greens and cook until just wilted, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of olive oil.
• When the oil is hot, cook tofu, turning occasionally, 4-5 minutes.
• Return vegetables to the pan. Reduce heat to low, then add teriyaki sauce mixture and cook, gently tossing, until combined, 1 minute.

• Divide rapid rice between bowls. Top with teriyaki prawn and ginger veggie stir-fry. Serve with any remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!
